[3] USA (Texas): child exposure
Date: Mon 22 Aug 2022 9:24 ET
Source: The US Sun [edited]
https://www.the-sun.com/health/6050551/mystery-toddler-catches-monkeypox-desperate/


The state of Texas has 1079 infections [now 1430 ] and officials there have revealed that a 2-year-old has the bug. It's not yet clear how the child contracted the virus as the little one does not attend nursery or school.

Medics in Harris County are undertaking contact tracing to find out who may have had direct contact with the child.

Judge Lina Hidalgo [County Executive] said the parents first noticed their child had a rash and took them to get checked out by a GP. Aside from the rash, the child has been asymptomatic, ABC13 reported.

Judge Hidalgo is now encouraging parents to be vigilant amid the current outbreak. "I understand that it's a very scary thing, and parents have concerns, and what we need to make sure is to be vigilant and understand the risks, not assume the worst. "But this reminds us that this is very real," she said.

The bug is more severe in young children and the Centre for Disease Control (CDC) has warned of preliminary evidence that has suggested children below the age of 8 could develop a more severe reaction to the virus.

Young children with eczema and other skin conditions, and children with immunocompromising conditions may also be at more risk for severe illness, according to the CDC.

The current assumption is that the child caught the bug through household transmission.

The latest case of the illness in a child comes after a study found that the virus can linger on surfaces touched by an infected person. Meaning the child could have contracted the bug if someone in their household had it.

Medics last week [week of 15 Aug 2022] also warned that the more cases that are identified -- the more likely it would be that children start to catch it.

--
